@Node program "Starting STDB"

 Starting STDB
 -------------
 STDB is started by double clicking the Icon.


 First Running of STDB
 ---------------------
 When run for the first time, it brings up a screenmode requester. You can
 select any 640x512 mode (Multiscan, CGX, etc.).

 This mode is stored in the comment of the STDB file, so if you wish to
 change the screenmode, simply clear the comment field.


 When first ran, new index files will be created, this does take quite a
 while, but is only done when first run or when updated files are used for
 the first time.

@EndNode

@Node control "Mouse & Keyboard Controls"

 Mouse & Keyboard Controls
 -------------------------
 Most functions are usually operated by clicking on a button or highlighted
 text with the Left Mouse Button.

 Keyboard use.

 'ESC'  - Quits program

 'r'    - 'Retraces' through the pages. (Same as 'parent' button)
 's'    - Enter 'Search' mode. (Same as Find)
 'n'    - Find the next occurence of search.
 't'    - Goto top of this page.
 'b'    - Goto Bottom of this page.

 ','    - Go to the page backward to this in the database. (Left arrow)
 '.'    - Go to the page forward to this in the database. (Right arrow)

 CrsUp  - Scroll Up. (Up Arrow)
 CrsDwn - Scroll Down. (Down Arrow)

@EndNode

@Node Display "Main Display"

 Main Display
 ------------
 Find  - Enter the text to find.
       - Find next occurence of search.

 Info  - Gives info about STDB & database

 Main  - Go to then First Page of the databse.

 Quit  - Quit program (of course ;)


 A - Z   - Goto a Index page of letter.

 TOS-VOY - Goto the page for desired series.
   A-Z   - Goto list of all episodes.

 TRIVIA  - Goto trivia pages.

@EndNode

@Node create "Creating Text Files"

 Creating Text Files
 -------------------

 All commands begin with '@', below i will insert a space where needed to allow
 amigaguide to display text.

 (Needless to say don't include the space when you write any commands)

 Begin a new page with '@page', followed by it's own uniqueID description.
 You can also follow it with "Title of page" (if required)

   E.G.   @page jelien "Jennifer Lien"


 Each line of text should be formatted to a width of 90 characters
 then add link tags.

 A link to another page is @ {"Text in link"uniqueID}

 Highlighted is similar but instead of the 'uniqueID' use '&' symbol.

 For a link to a picture/sample instead of 'uniqueID' use '*' followed by
 path+name of pictur/sample.

   E.G.   @ {"Kes"*stv/_kes}

 A paths are based on the directory the STDB is in, unless device is in filepath

   E.G.   @ {"Kes"*dh5:stv/_kes}

 See @{"Picture format" link picture} to see dimensions of pictures

 Samples must be 8SVX type.


 Your saved text files can be added to filelist of mainfile by inserting

   @file 'filename' into top of mainfile.


 If there is no 'uniqueID' in the link then the text from that link will be
 used as the 'uniqueID'.

   E.G.   @ {"Sensor"} - will link to a page that was defined by
                         @page sensor

 Look at my files to see how I've used links etc.

 (not the demo ones as they are full of missing and deliberate deadend links)

@EndNode

@Node pictures "Adding Pictures"

 Adding Pictures
 ---------------
 Any picture can be in any format you have a datatype for.

 Pics must only use colours 32-254 of the colourmap.
 Also must be 160*128.

 I personally use 'GFXCON2' to convert a file to required size and colours, then
 use 'DT2RGFX' to convert it to RGFX format

 I have two buttons on 'DOpus' set up as follows.

 1.  c:gfxcon2 {fu} TO {d}{o} colors 255 offset 32 size 160 128

 2.  c:dt2rgfx {fu} TO {d}{o} XPK MASH

@EndNode

@Node ttypes "Tooltypes"

 Tooltypes
 ---------

 Two tooltypes are used.

 NOT TAKEN INTO ACCOUNT IN DEMO VERSION - ALSO DEFAULT=YES

 CHECK=YES|NO  - check if a filelink exists before displaying link.
                 If available display as a link.
                 If not available the display as nornmal text.
                 DEFAULT-NO


 FLASH=YES|NO  - If a filelink doesn't exist and the text of a link is '*'
                 then display the '*' in black (invisible) or as flashing
                 colour.
                 DEFAULT-NO

@ENDNODE

